        "issued": "2026-05-08T10:00:00+00:00",
        "effectiveDateTime": "2026-05-08T10:00:00+00:00",
        "conclusion": "CLINICAL INDICATION: 57-year-old male, smoker, routine follow-up chest CT.\n\nTECHNIQUE: CT of the chest with intravenous contrast.\n\nFINDINGS:\nLUNGS: A spiculated right upper lobe nodule measuring 2.3 x 1.9 cm is identified in the right upper lobe, anterior segment. The nodule demonstrates irregular margins and pleural tethering. There is ipsilateral mediastinal lymphadenopathy with a right paratracheal node measuring 1.8 x 1.4 cm (short axis). No contralateral adenopathy. No pleural effusion.\n\nPRIOR IMAGING: No prior chest CT available for comparison.\n\nIMPRESSION:\n1. 2.3 cm spiculated right upper lobe nodule with ipsilateral mediastinal adenopathy \u2014 highly suspicious for primary lung malignancy. PET-CT and tissue sampling recommended within 24-48 hours.\n2. Findings represent at minimum stage IIA disease pending further workup."
      },
